 should\ni be disciplined and muzzled or not\ni until next week. It is generally be\nlieved he will receive a dose of the\nmedicine given Rdsr Admirals Sims\n1 and Bradley A. Fiske several years\n1 ago.\nEX-RftFEXPEBT\nHUNGS SELF.\nFuneral arrangements for Thomas\nH. CaHH, S\u00ab, X-ray teehnican at\nthe Mount Alto Veterans Hospital,\n1 who hung himself to a rafter at\nhis Bethesda home, will be. made\ntoday after the widow visits Pum\nphrey# Undertaking Parlors at\nRockville where the body has been\nprepared for burial.\nCahill hss been in ill health for\nsometime and yesterday reported to\n1 Walter Reed Hospital for diagnosis\nand treatment. Hospital authorities\nflatly refused to give any infor\nmation as to the ailihent from\nWhk-h he was suffering.\n1 After being assigned to a cot.\nhe is said to have left the hos\npital yesterday afternoon.\nThe body was discovered by Mrs.\ni Cahill about 6 o\u2019clock when she\nreturned from the Government de\npartment where she works.\nMrs. Cahill summoned a physician\nwho said Mr. Cahill has been dead\nj for several hours.\nSergt. Leroy Rodgers of the\nBethesda sub station. Montgomery\ncounty police, investigated and re\nported to State's Attorney Robert\ni Peter, jr. Peter later stated that\ni|o inquest would be necessary.\n\u201cVIRGINIA DYNASTY\u201d\nThe Virginia Dynasty wax the\nriven to the three\nX iden t \u00df \u2014Jottoraon. Mad-\nw^22 r 7*~* Who CCupie< th*\nwnite House for nearly a quarter\n1 A o^rtwnr\u2014l\u00df\u00dfl to 1825.\u2014The\nPathfinder.\"\nj \"\"\"\"\u201c^wsass^Me\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014 1\nKlgb Lew Qeee Oom\ni Universal Pipe it# 25 26#\ni U 8 Cast j p.. \u00bb7 3WX 287 204\ni 1 8 Distrlbut.. 18# 18# 18#\ni US Hoffman.. 53 50# S 3 51\nUS A1c0h01.,.. 77# 73# ?7# 78\ni \u00dcBLeather... if# is#\ni U S Leath A.. 43# 41 41# 40J<\nU S Lm pri pr 96# 97# 98# 97\n1 v S Real Im* 82# 60# 62# 62\nUS Rubber.... 56# 66# 56# 55#\nUSRubtet.*.. 101# 100# I\u00abf# Iflo#\ni USoteol... M> if2# 151# 162# 151#\n